@startuml
title Content Caching Flow - Complete Sequence
autonumber
actor "Client (App/Web)" as Client
participant "API Gateway" as Gateway
participant "Content Service" as Service
participant "Cache (Redis)" as Cache
database "Database (PostgreSQL)" as DB
participant "Content Sync" as Watcher
queue "Kafka" as Kafka

== Scenario 1: Cache Hit (Fast Path) ==

Client -> Gateway: GET /content/{id}
activate Gateway

Gateway -> Service: Forward request
activate Service

Service -> Cache: GET content:movie:{id}
activate Cache

Cache --> Service: JSON data (HIT)\nTTL remaining: 120s
deactivate Cache

Service --> Gateway: 200 OK
deactivate Service

Gateway --> Client: 200 OK\n{content data}
deactivate Gateway



== Scenario 2: Cache Miss (Slow Path) ==

Client -> Gateway: GET /content/{id}
activate Gateway

Gateway -> Service: Forward request
activate Service

Service -> Cache: GET content:movie:{id}
activate Cache

Cache --> Service: null (MISS)
deactivate Cache

Service -> DB: SELECT c.*, md.* \nFROM content c\nLEFT JOIN movie_details md \nON c.id = md.content_id\nWHERE c.id = {id} AND c.type = 'movie'
activate DB

DB --> Service: content row + movie_details
deactivate DB

Service -> Cache: SET content:movie:{id} JSON\n TTL 5 min
activate Cache

Cache --> Service: OK
deactivate Cache

Service --> Gateway: 200 OK
deactivate Service

Gateway --> Client: 200 OK\n{content data}
deactivate Gateway

note right: Response time: <100ms

== Scenario 3: Cache Invalidation on Update ==

box "Database Update Flow" #LightBlue
DB -> Watcher: NOTIFY content_updated\n{id, type, operation: 'UPDATE'}
activate Watcher

Watcher -> DB: SELECT c.*, md.* \nFROM content c\nWHERE c.id = {id}
activate DB
DB --> Watcher: Updated content data
deactivate DB

Watcher -> Cache: DELETE content:movie:{id}
activate Cache
Cache --> Watcher: OK (deleted)
deactivate Cache

Watcher -> Kafka: PUBLISH content.updated\n{\n  "id": "{id}",\n  "type": "movie",\n  "operation": "UPDATE",\n  "timestamp": "2024-01-20T10:30:00Z"\n}
deactivate Watcher
end box

note right: Other services react:\n- Search Service (reindex)\n- Recommendation Service (update)\n- Analytics Service (track)

@enduml
